WEBVTT

00:02.102 --> 00:03.670
- ♪ Hey ♪

00:03.737 --> 00:05.505
♪ Come on ♪

00:05.572 --> 00:07.173
♪ Time for
the Duda Brothers ♪

00:07.240 --> 00:08.742
- ♪ You know what
time it is ♪

00:08.808 --> 00:10.009
{\an5}- ♪ You know what
time it is ♪

00:10.076 --> 00:11.211
- ♪ One, two ♪

00:11.277 --> 00:12.879
♪ One, two, three ♪

00:12.946 --> 00:15.382
♪ You know what
time it is ♪

00:15.448 --> 00:16.750
♪ Hey ♪

00:16.816 --> 00:18.451
♪ Duda time ♪

00:18.518 --> 00:19.452
♪ Hey ♪

00:19.519 --> 00:20.687
♪ Duda... ♪

00:20.754 --> 00:22.722
♪ Brothers ♪

00:22.789 --> 00:24.190
♪ Duda ♪

00:24.257 --> 00:26.192
♪ You know what time it is ♪
- ♪ Duda time ♪

00:26.259 --> 00:28.161
♪ You know what
time it is ♪

00:28.228 --> 00:29.829
- Ready?
- Let's go.

00:31.798 --> 00:33.600
- [classical music]

00:33.666 --> 00:35.301
- [swords clanging]

00:35.368 --> 00:38.638
{\an8}- Welcome to my Castle Mania
birthday party--

00:38.705 --> 00:42.642
{\an8}also known as the best night
of your young lives...

00:42.709 --> 00:44.244
{\an8}I hope.

00:44.310 --> 00:47.380
{\an8}This is my chance to show my new
classmates that I belong.

00:47.447 --> 00:49.416
{\an8}I mean, it won't be easy
topping Carter, though.

00:49.482 --> 00:52.452
{\an8}He always throws the most
epic birthday parties.

00:52.519 --> 00:55.555
{\an8}Last weekend he sent us
all home with a puppy.

00:55.622 --> 00:57.791
{\an8}This is Mr. Wigglebutt.

00:57.857 --> 01:00.226
{\an8}I've never hated
anything so cute.

01:02.629 --> 01:06.032
{\an8}- There's so much hay!

01:06.099 --> 01:07.400
{\an8}- I've seen more.

01:07.467 --> 01:09.102
{\an8}- This is the first time
we've ever been

01:09.169 --> 01:10.870
{\an8}to one of Sam's
birthday parties.

01:10.937 --> 01:12.539
{\an8}Too bad we can only stay
for a few minutes.

01:12.605 --> 01:13.773
{\an8}- It's nothing personal.

01:13.840 --> 01:16.042
{\an8}It's just we have, like,
eight other parties today.

01:16.109 --> 01:17.243
{\an8}- I thought it was nine.

01:17.310 --> 01:20.280
{\an8}- Jenny Meyers got grounded.
- She did not.

01:21.514 --> 01:25.418
{\an8}- GIGI: There it is--
Ye Olde Royal Challenge.

01:25.485 --> 01:27.053
- What's that?

01:27.120 --> 01:28.788
- It's the reason I came.

01:28.855 --> 01:30.290
Well, and Sam's birthday,
of course.

01:30.356 --> 01:32.859
All I have to do is eat
a steak, a dozen waffles,

01:32.926 --> 01:35.995
three chili dogs, celery,
a bucket of bacon, and a cherry,

01:36.062 --> 01:40.967
and then they put my name on
this wall in permanent marker--

01:41.034 --> 01:43.736
which is, like, forever.

01:43.803 --> 01:45.472
Think I can do it?

01:45.538 --> 01:46.906
- I know you can--

01:46.973 --> 01:48.575
'cause I'm gonna
be your coach.

01:48.641 --> 01:50.710
It's all about mind
over matter...

01:50.777 --> 01:52.045
facing your fears...

01:52.111 --> 01:54.314
not counting your chickens
before they hatch!

01:54.380 --> 01:56.015
- Okay, maybe we should
save some of this

01:56.082 --> 01:58.218
for when the food comes.

01:58.284 --> 02:03.156
{\an8}- So, dude, how are you
paying for all of this?

02:03.223 --> 02:05.658
{\an8}- Gift card from Grandma.

02:05.725 --> 02:07.227
{\an8}It's for two hundred bucks.

02:07.293 --> 02:10.029
{\an8}- Wow, Mo-Mo got monay.

02:10.096 --> 02:11.331
{\an8}- This is gonna be great!

02:11.397 --> 02:13.233
We can tour
the Dungeon of Doom

02:13.299 --> 02:15.401
and climb the chocolate
lava fountain.

02:15.468 --> 02:18.338
Wait, do seventh
graders like chocolate lava?

02:18.404 --> 02:20.807
- Just relax and be yourself.

02:20.874 --> 02:24.143
{\an8}You get a little crazy when
you're trying to impress people.

02:24.210 --> 02:27.413
{\an8}Like that time at camp
you tried to lead the hike.

02:27.480 --> 02:30.650
{\an8}- Hey, we got to spend
an extra night outside.

02:30.717 --> 02:32.318
{\an8}It was beautiful.

02:32.385 --> 02:33.753
- Oh.

02:37.290 --> 02:38.558
- [pounding staff]

02:38.625 --> 02:41.194
- Would you like any
appetizers, Your Majesty?

02:41.261 --> 02:43.129
- Bring us mozzarella sticks.

02:43.196 --> 02:44.864
- Mozzarella sticks?

02:44.931 --> 02:46.533
Reminds me of my birthday--

02:46.599 --> 02:50.003
when I was two.

02:50.069 --> 02:53.039
- Um, yeah, what was
I thinking?

02:53.106 --> 02:54.941
Um...bring us meatballs!

02:55.008 --> 02:57.343
And who wants a t-shirt?
- I do!

02:57.410 --> 02:59.546
- Put it on the gift card.

02:59.612 --> 03:03.316
Anything you guys want,
it's on me.

03:03.383 --> 03:05.585
- Sam, don't you think you're
going a bit overboard?

03:05.652 --> 03:10.557
- Quiet, peasant, or I'll make
you walk the plank.

03:10.623 --> 03:12.025
- What?

03:12.091 --> 03:14.093
- I don't know what
a king says.

03:14.160 --> 03:16.162
- Happy birthday,
your Royal Highness!

03:16.229 --> 03:18.131
- [fanfare music]

03:18.197 --> 03:20.233
- [present thuds]

03:20.300 --> 03:21.935
- It's the rock you
used as a pillow

03:22.001 --> 03:24.537
when you got us
lost at camp.

03:26.105 --> 03:28.908
- [tiny bugle tooting]

03:28.975 --> 03:30.877
- Ye Olde Royal Challenge.

03:33.079 --> 03:34.514
- Okay, first things first.

03:34.581 --> 03:36.382
We're gonna need about
a hundred napkins.

03:38.651 --> 03:42.488
- Gigi, all that food,
it's on me,

03:42.555 --> 03:44.724
and, Dallas, I'm paying
for those napkins.

03:44.791 --> 03:48.061
- I think they're free,
but thanks.

03:48.127 --> 03:49.729
- How's your night
going, Glenn?

03:49.796 --> 03:52.999
- Pretty good,
but I ran outta milk.

03:53.066 --> 03:55.301
- Ah...
[clapping hands]

03:55.368 --> 03:57.537
No, you didn't.

03:57.604 --> 04:05.244
- ♪

04:05.311 --> 04:07.880
- [glugging]

04:07.947 --> 04:12.852
- So, Carter, thanks for coming
to my amazing birthday party.

04:12.919 --> 04:14.253
- Amazing?
- Yeah.

04:14.320 --> 04:16.422
- There are no more
turkey legs.

04:16.488 --> 04:21.094
- ♪

04:21.160 --> 04:23.062
- Let--

04:23.129 --> 04:26.165
- But that's Tyler's
turkey leg.

04:26.232 --> 04:28.301
- There you go.

04:29.836 --> 04:31.437
- Hey, Sam, I'm sorry,
we gotta jet.

04:31.504 --> 04:33.272
- But we're just
getting started.

04:33.339 --> 04:36.009
- Sorry, but weekends
are cra-zy.

04:36.075 --> 04:37.644
- You know what?

04:37.710 --> 04:40.179
I saw a tiara and
a sword in the gift shop.

04:40.246 --> 04:41.681
How 'bout you put it
on the bill?

04:41.748 --> 04:44.617
- Maybe we can stay
for a few more minutes.

04:47.453 --> 04:50.657
- All is well in my kingdom.

04:50.723 --> 04:52.625
- Sam, you know
you don't have to

04:52.692 --> 04:54.293
spend money
to impress people.

04:54.360 --> 04:55.762
Slow down.

04:55.828 --> 04:58.064
And this is Tyler Duda
telling you to slow down,

04:58.131 --> 05:01.067
so you know it's serious.

05:01.134 --> 05:03.469
- I know what this is about.

05:03.536 --> 05:05.605
I didn't get you anything.

05:05.672 --> 05:07.240
[clapping hands]

05:08.808 --> 05:11.177
[clapping hands]

05:11.244 --> 05:13.046
Well, the waiter must
be in the bathroom.

05:13.112 --> 05:14.714
But, don't worry,

05:14.781 --> 05:17.016
I saw a stuffed unicorn with
your name written all over it.

05:17.083 --> 05:23.856
- ♪

05:23.923 --> 05:28.728
- Your Majesty,
the bill comes to $300.07.

05:28.795 --> 05:31.831
- Three hundred dollars?!
- And seven cents.

05:31.898 --> 05:33.566
- How is that possible?

05:33.633 --> 05:36.102
I had a gift card for $200.

05:36.169 --> 05:38.337
- Uh, it was actually for $20.

05:38.404 --> 05:41.007
- Aw, Mo-Mo!

05:41.074 --> 05:42.608
I can't pay that.

05:42.675 --> 05:45.678
- Something wrong with your
little birthday party, Sam?

05:45.745 --> 05:47.046
- Wrong?

05:47.113 --> 05:48.448
I'll tell you what's wrong.

05:48.514 --> 05:50.483
We need more apps.
- KIDS: Yeah!

05:50.550 --> 05:52.418
- [quietly] Please don't
bring us more apps.

05:57.090 --> 05:58.524
I should have
listened to Tyler

05:58.591 --> 06:00.526
and not gotten
so carried away.

06:00.593 --> 06:03.863
But I cannot let my friends
find out about that bill.

06:03.930 --> 06:06.299
- Okay, I'm gonna need
that crown back.

06:10.837 --> 06:12.839
- Come on, I gotta
have a quarter.

06:12.905 --> 06:14.807
- Hey, Sam, the waiters
were just talking about

06:14.874 --> 06:17.276
this kid who can't
pay his bill.

06:17.343 --> 06:20.179
What a dummy.
- Huh?

06:20.246 --> 06:22.181
That's great.

06:22.248 --> 06:23.716
Do you have $300
I could borrow?

06:23.783 --> 06:26.819
- Oh! So, you're
the broke birthday boy.

06:26.886 --> 06:28.988
- I know, I know.

06:29.055 --> 06:30.289
You were right.

06:30.356 --> 06:32.091
- I am right, like,
half of the time.

06:32.158 --> 06:35.595
But don't worry, what's
the worst they can do to you?

06:35.661 --> 06:40.133
- You must defeat
the Knight of the Unpaid Bill!

06:40.199 --> 06:41.501
- Hey, is that him?

06:41.567 --> 06:43.703
- Oh, no, that's Ralph.
He works in the kitchen.

06:43.770 --> 06:45.071
- Hi, Ralph!

06:47.974 --> 06:50.176
- That's the Knight
of the Unpaid Bill.

06:50.243 --> 06:52.512
- [dramatic music]

06:52.578 --> 06:55.748
- Defeat the knight and your
birthday party is free.

06:55.815 --> 06:57.016
- Free?

06:57.083 --> 06:58.217
Oh, that sounds good.

06:58.284 --> 07:00.353
- No one has ever
defeated him.

07:00.419 --> 07:02.622
- Oh...see if they'll
let you fight Ralph.

07:02.688 --> 07:04.657
- You may not fight Ralph!

07:08.694 --> 07:11.464
- I'm so proud of you, Gigi.

07:11.531 --> 07:14.934
Who knew your little
tummy was so big?

07:15.001 --> 07:17.136
- I think I can do this.

07:17.203 --> 07:19.639
- [tray thuds]
- I can't do this.

07:21.474 --> 07:23.276
- Happy birthday to who?

07:23.342 --> 07:24.811
Not me.

07:24.877 --> 07:27.580
- Hey, we're the only two who
know you can't pay the bill.

07:27.647 --> 07:30.550
Just beat the knight
and everything will be great.

07:30.616 --> 07:33.352
- But no one's ever
beaten him before.

07:33.419 --> 07:35.354
- Oh, yeah, I forgot
about that.

07:35.421 --> 07:36.956
- Hey, Sam,
hope you don't mind,

07:37.023 --> 07:39.125
but, I got another sword.

07:39.192 --> 07:40.793
- And I got another tiara.

07:40.860 --> 07:43.396
We're definitely
staying now.

07:43.462 --> 07:45.097
- Sam, what are you doing?

07:45.164 --> 07:46.299
Dressing up in
a suit of armor

07:46.365 --> 07:49.035
and fighting for
our entertainment?

07:49.101 --> 07:52.438
- Oh, yeah, that's exactly
what I'm doing.

07:52.505 --> 07:55.708
It's all a part of
the VIP experience.

07:55.775 --> 07:58.511
- It never ends!
My medieval mind is blown!

07:58.578 --> 07:59.912
- This is foam.

07:59.979 --> 08:02.582
How am I supposed to defend
myself with foam?

08:02.648 --> 08:04.517
- Yeah, we're not allowed
to use real weapons anymore.

08:04.584 --> 08:06.986
Uh, I'd tell you why,
but it would just make you sad.

08:07.053 --> 08:10.189
- This birthday party's
starting to fall apart.

08:10.256 --> 08:12.358
Now I'm having fun.

08:12.425 --> 08:14.927
Oh, birthday mug last year.

08:14.994 --> 08:16.028
[sipping drink]

08:16.095 --> 08:18.998
- Gigi, Dallas,
Sam's taking on a knight.

08:19.065 --> 08:22.268
- Be there after
I finish this bacon--

08:22.335 --> 08:24.170
if I finish this bacon.

08:24.237 --> 08:26.439
- Go out and empty
out that bucket.

08:26.505 --> 08:29.108
I feel like we're gonna
need it later.

08:29.175 --> 08:31.811
- [huge burp]

08:31.878 --> 08:33.011
Excuse me.

08:33.078 --> 08:37.549
- CROWD:
[applauding]

08:37.616 --> 08:39.585
- KNIGHT:
[snarling]

08:39.652 --> 08:42.188
- Oh, man...
- [armor clanking]

08:42.255 --> 08:47.593
- ♪

08:47.660 --> 08:49.829
- Bet you've never
seen anyone

08:49.896 --> 08:51.831
get pummeled by
a knight before.

08:51.898 --> 08:54.400
- TYLER: Sam isn't doing
too good out there.

08:54.467 --> 08:56.969
- No, he isn't.

08:57.036 --> 08:58.504
I mean, get him, Sam!

08:58.571 --> 09:00.473
- BOTH:
[grunting]

09:00.539 --> 09:02.341
- Hey, maybe we should
help fight that knight.

09:02.408 --> 09:04.043
I mean, it is included
in the party.

09:04.110 --> 09:07.747
- Yeah, and we owe Sam
for this bonkers birthday.

09:07.813 --> 09:09.482
- Oh, for the love
of Mo-Mo...

09:09.548 --> 09:11.183
- Princess Sophia
wants to rumble.

09:11.250 --> 09:12.718
[knuckles cracking]

09:12.785 --> 09:18.024
- ♪

09:18.090 --> 09:21.294
- Oh, you're not
a very nice knight.

09:21.360 --> 09:24.830
- KNIGHT:
[roaring]

09:24.897 --> 09:26.532
- [sword clangs]
- CROWD: [gasps]

09:26.599 --> 09:30.403
- Nobody messes with
my brother on his birthday!

09:30.469 --> 09:33.005
- [armor clanking]
- KNIGHT: Ow! Ow!

09:33.072 --> 09:34.540
What are you doing?

09:34.607 --> 09:35.841
- Beating you with
a piece of bread.

09:35.908 --> 09:38.077
- I'm the princess
of this castle!

09:38.144 --> 09:41.547
- KNIGHT: Hey, you know
this is fake, right?

09:41.614 --> 09:44.450
- It's corn time!
- [armor clanking]

09:44.517 --> 09:46.419
- I'm helping, too!

09:46.485 --> 09:48.454
Oh!

09:48.521 --> 09:50.990
Darn, I missed.

09:51.057 --> 09:53.626
- [armor clanking]

09:53.693 --> 09:56.128
- If you wanna call
security on any of them,

09:56.195 --> 09:57.663
I won't stop you.

09:57.730 --> 10:01.567
- Get that knight! Yeah!
- KNIGHT: Ahhhh!

10:01.634 --> 10:04.570
- Oh, man, that's brutal!

10:04.637 --> 10:06.405
- KNIGHT:
I quit!

10:06.472 --> 10:09.141
This isn't
worth nine bucks an hour.

10:09.208 --> 10:11.477
- Woo!
- ALL: [cheering]

10:11.544 --> 10:13.646
- Happy birthday, bro.

10:14.814 --> 10:16.849
- Okay, don't celebrate
just yet.

10:16.916 --> 10:19.285
There's still one more
thing you have to do.

10:23.823 --> 10:27.460
- Well, my plan to have a big-
shot birthday party failed.

10:27.526 --> 10:29.328
Dry.

10:29.395 --> 10:30.863
- You don't need
knights and wizards

10:30.930 --> 10:32.665
to have a great birthday.

10:32.732 --> 10:34.734
All you need
is to be yourself.

10:34.800 --> 10:38.404
And a little bit
of soap and water.

10:38.471 --> 10:40.573
- KIDS:
[gasping]

10:40.639 --> 10:44.643
[laughing]

10:47.680 --> 10:49.582
- I've been to a million
birthday parties.

10:49.648 --> 10:51.450
But this one's
the craziest.

10:51.517 --> 10:54.153
- I can't wait
for next year.

10:54.220 --> 10:56.589
- This is good, clean fun!

10:56.655 --> 10:59.158
- You guys are having fun?

10:59.225 --> 11:01.060
We're washing dishes.

11:01.127 --> 11:03.162
At my party, everybody
got to ride zebras.

11:06.365 --> 11:09.335
- Looks like you're the king
of seventh grade, bro.

11:09.402 --> 11:11.570
- SAM: Tyler!!
[laughing]

11:11.637 --> 11:14.673
It's good to be the king.

11:16.675 --> 11:17.610
- [bell ringing]

11:19.645 --> 11:22.648
- In just a few hours, I'll own
a brand new Next Watch.

11:22.715 --> 11:25.785
It's gonna help me control
my busy seventh grade life.

11:25.851 --> 11:27.987
- What's so great about
the Next Watch?

11:28.054 --> 11:29.455
- Are you kidding?

11:29.522 --> 11:34.126
It's gonna replace my phone,
my computer, and my old watch.

11:34.193 --> 11:35.995
Hm, goodbye, old watch.
[chuckles]

11:36.062 --> 11:37.163
- BOY: Ow!

11:37.229 --> 11:39.999
- Ooh. Sorry, Chuck.

11:40.066 --> 11:41.934
You can keep that.

11:44.403 --> 11:46.572
Is that a mime?

11:46.639 --> 11:49.642
- Yeah. That TV show,
"Kids Are Amazing at Stuff,"

11:49.708 --> 11:51.544
they're having auditions here.

11:51.610 --> 11:54.313
Good thing I'm a kid
who's amazing at stuff.

11:54.380 --> 11:56.515
- Why do you care about
being on that show anyway?

11:56.582 --> 11:59.085
- Sam, ever since you
started seventh grade,

11:59.151 --> 12:00.386
you've been killin' it--

12:00.453 --> 12:03.222
which is great, but I miss
having my own thing,

12:03.289 --> 12:05.724
which is being super,
super famous.

12:05.791 --> 12:09.061
I used to be the face
of "Extreme Flakes!"

12:09.128 --> 12:10.529
Take it to the extreme!

12:10.596 --> 12:11.897
Extreme!

12:11.964 --> 12:14.233
Yeah! Yeah!

12:14.300 --> 12:17.036
It gave me a taste
of fame--

12:17.103 --> 12:19.238
and it tasted so sweet.

12:19.305 --> 12:21.273
[rattling cereal box]

12:21.340 --> 12:23.342
- Well, what are you gonna
do for an audition?

12:23.409 --> 12:24.610
Balloon art?

12:24.677 --> 12:26.145
Gymnastics?

12:26.212 --> 12:27.480
Jump through a flaming
hoop on a cheetah?

12:27.546 --> 12:29.648
- If I could do any
of those things,

12:29.715 --> 12:31.684
do you think I'd be talking
to you right now?

12:31.750 --> 12:33.552
I have to do something
unbelievable.

12:33.619 --> 12:36.021
- Well, maybe you should
get a partner.

12:36.088 --> 12:37.590
Ask Carter.

12:37.656 --> 12:40.126
You two did that incredible
martial arts act.

12:40.192 --> 12:42.228
- Yeah. Carter.

12:42.294 --> 12:43.963
That's an idea.

12:44.029 --> 12:45.865
A terrible idea!

12:45.931 --> 12:48.033
Carter's way too serious.

12:48.100 --> 12:49.702
He doesn't know
how to have fun.

12:49.768 --> 12:52.671
There's got to be
someone else.

12:52.738 --> 12:59.111
- ♪

12:59.178 --> 13:00.379
- Hi, I'm Elmer,

13:00.446 --> 13:03.182
and this is Little Elmer.

13:03.249 --> 13:06.018
- Okay, how are you
doing, Little Elmer?

13:06.085 --> 13:08.687
- Yeah, he...doesn't talk.

13:09.822 --> 13:12.691
- And now to pull a rabbit
out of my hat.

13:16.262 --> 13:17.997
He's not in here.

13:18.063 --> 13:20.599
Oh, no, Mr. Fluffington!

13:20.666 --> 13:22.434
- Okay...

13:22.501 --> 13:25.137
- I can eat cake.
[munching]

13:25.204 --> 13:27.806
- Yep, that's a lotta cake.

13:27.873 --> 13:29.575
Huh?

13:29.642 --> 13:32.611
- ♪

13:32.678 --> 13:34.413
- Well, 400 East
Orange Street.

13:34.480 --> 13:36.348
Here we are.

13:36.415 --> 13:39.351
- Um, I don't think this
is an electronics store.

13:39.418 --> 13:41.387
- It looks like
a dentist's office.

13:41.453 --> 13:45.958
- That's probably because
it is a dentist's office.

13:46.025 --> 13:50.796
- Cool! We can get a Next Watch
and get our teeth cleaned.

13:50.863 --> 13:52.698
- Guys, I'm sorry.

13:52.765 --> 13:54.266
I was wrong.

13:54.333 --> 13:56.936
The address was
400 West Orange Street.

13:57.002 --> 13:58.704
- That's on the other
side of town!

13:58.771 --> 14:01.006
We gotta hurry.
The line's gonna be insane.

14:01.073 --> 14:07.313
- ♪

14:07.379 --> 14:09.381
- Carter's not that great.

14:14.253 --> 14:15.888
All right, he's pretty good.

14:17.423 --> 14:19.358
Hey, Carter, buddy!
What's up?

14:19.425 --> 14:22.761
- "Buddy?" You must want
something real bad.

14:22.828 --> 14:24.230
- No.

14:24.296 --> 14:26.532
Hey, I like your costume.

14:26.599 --> 14:27.933
Is that cotton?

14:28.000 --> 14:29.368
What a soft choice.

14:29.435 --> 14:30.869
- You're acting weird.

14:30.936 --> 14:32.338
- Me? Weird?

14:32.404 --> 14:33.505
What? No.

14:33.572 --> 14:35.674
Hey, uh, I was thinking,

14:35.741 --> 14:38.244
we should put our martial
arts act back together.

14:38.310 --> 14:40.012
Sound fun? Great.

14:40.079 --> 14:44.083
In first grade, Carter
and I were the Karate Kids,

14:44.149 --> 14:47.419
an amazing martial arts group.

14:47.486 --> 14:49.855
But Carter was way
too serious.

14:54.226 --> 14:57.263
- I am not putting
the Karate Kids back together.

14:57.329 --> 14:59.298
Working with you
was a disaster.

14:59.365 --> 15:01.000
You never took
things seriously.

15:01.066 --> 15:04.336
And when was the last
time you even did karate?

15:04.403 --> 15:06.505
- Hi-ya!

15:06.572 --> 15:08.073
About two seconds ago.

15:08.140 --> 15:12.011
Listen, "Kids are Amazing at
Stuff," they're coming here.

15:12.077 --> 15:13.512
We could be on that show.

15:13.579 --> 15:14.947
- No, thanks.

15:15.014 --> 15:16.415
- Okay.

15:16.482 --> 15:21.020
Please, please, Carter,
I need you, please!

15:21.086 --> 15:22.588
- Fine.

15:22.655 --> 15:25.124
- Please, please--
wait, what?

15:25.190 --> 15:27.359
I can't believe
he said yes.

15:27.426 --> 15:30.029
Wait, why did he say yes?

15:30.095 --> 15:32.598
- I have my reasons.

15:32.665 --> 15:34.500
- Listen guys,
I'm really sorry

15:34.566 --> 15:36.468
that I took us
to the wrong place.

15:36.535 --> 15:38.570
But I promise
I'm gonna get us there.

15:38.637 --> 15:40.005
- No worries, Sam.

15:40.072 --> 15:41.307
But pick up the pace.

15:41.373 --> 15:43.809
- Yeah, put your back
in to it, man.

15:46.512 --> 15:49.581
- Finally! We're here.

15:49.648 --> 15:52.618
- Those two hours
just flew by.

15:52.685 --> 15:55.554
- So many hills. It was
like a roller coaster!

15:55.621 --> 15:57.523
- Okay, let's go...

15:57.589 --> 16:00.993
get in the longest line
I've ever seen in my life.

16:03.962 --> 16:06.665
- Okay, we have to rehearse
for the audition.

16:06.732 --> 16:08.701
I choreographed our routine.

16:08.767 --> 16:10.736
- Yeah, and I have
a couple of ideas, too.

16:10.803 --> 16:12.838
- Just stand behind me
and do what I do.

16:22.481 --> 16:35.561
- ♪

16:35.627 --> 16:38.097
- [ceiling tile clanks]

16:38.163 --> 16:39.565
- Okay, this isn't fun.

16:39.631 --> 16:41.100
- You're not taking
this seriously.

16:41.166 --> 16:42.434
- All right, listen.

16:42.501 --> 16:43.936
I think we're spending
way too much time

16:44.002 --> 16:46.271
on the "karate" aspect
of Karate Kids.

16:46.338 --> 16:51.143
So, I took the liberty of
getting me a costume.

16:51.210 --> 16:53.746
And? And?

16:53.812 --> 16:56.515
- You're definitely
not taking this seriously.

16:56.582 --> 16:59.084
- Come on,
we're entertainers.

16:59.151 --> 17:01.353
- [disco music]

17:01.420 --> 17:03.922
- It's karate,
not Christmas.

17:03.989 --> 17:05.424
- I even got us
sound effects.

17:05.491 --> 17:09.361
- [sproinging,
whistling bomb, explosion]

17:09.428 --> 17:10.896
[cat meowing]

17:10.963 --> 17:13.932
- We don't have to use
the kitty, if we don't want.

17:13.999 --> 17:17.403
- I can't work with your stupid
jacket and sound effects.

17:17.469 --> 17:19.637
- I can't work with
you and your...

17:19.704 --> 17:21.573
awesome karate moves!

17:21.640 --> 17:23.909
- I'm going solo!
- Me, too!

17:23.976 --> 17:26.345
- [bomb whistling,
cat meowing, explosion]

17:26.412 --> 17:31.583
- ♪

17:31.650 --> 17:34.386
- Are we ever gonna get
to the front of the line?

17:34.453 --> 17:35.721
- We're almost there.

17:35.788 --> 17:37.389
It'll all be
worth it soon.

17:37.456 --> 17:38.791
- GIGI: Okay.

17:38.857 --> 17:41.894
[gasps]
She can't do that. No.

17:41.960 --> 17:44.396
That's against the rules--
of life!

17:44.463 --> 17:45.998
- Yeah.

17:46.064 --> 17:48.600
- She's gonna get real
bad line karma.

17:48.667 --> 17:50.035
- You know what?
I got this.

17:50.102 --> 17:52.538
[cracks knuckles]

17:52.604 --> 17:54.606
Excuse me, little girl?

17:54.673 --> 17:56.375
You kind of cut in
front of my friends.

17:56.442 --> 17:59.578
- Deal with it!
- [gasps]

17:59.645 --> 18:01.780
I'm out of ideas.

18:01.847 --> 18:03.715
- We can't let her get
away with this.

18:03.782 --> 18:05.884
Who wants to yell at
the adorable little girl?

18:07.820 --> 18:09.988
- There's only one
way to decide.

18:10.055 --> 18:11.857
- ALL:
Homeroom hand-slam!

18:11.924 --> 18:14.059
One-two-three, slam!

18:14.126 --> 18:18.564
- [imitates bulldozer rumbling]
Bulldozer. I win.

18:18.630 --> 18:20.532
No one ever does
"bulldozer,"

18:20.599 --> 18:22.167
but it always wins.

18:22.234 --> 18:24.403
Think outside
the rock box, people.

18:24.470 --> 18:26.905
- You're up, Gigi.

18:26.972 --> 18:27.973
- Oh...

18:28.040 --> 18:30.142
that's why no one
threw bulldozer.

18:32.711 --> 18:34.847
[exhales]

18:34.913 --> 18:36.982
Excuse me, little girl?

18:37.049 --> 18:39.451
You really have to go to
the back of the line.

18:39.518 --> 18:43.088
- Help me, help me,
this big girl is picking on me

18:43.155 --> 18:45.958
and trying to kick
me out of line!

18:46.024 --> 18:49.595
- No, no, it's just a...
a misunderstanding.

18:49.661 --> 18:53.198
- Nice try, amateur.

18:53.265 --> 18:55.234
- She's good.

18:55.300 --> 18:58.070
She's really good.

18:59.571 --> 19:01.507
- [whimsical music]

19:01.573 --> 19:06.245
♪

19:06.311 --> 19:08.180
- Hi-yah!

19:08.247 --> 19:12.150
- ♪

19:12.217 --> 19:14.720
- You're not gonna audition
on your own, are you?

19:14.786 --> 19:16.522
You look ridiculous.

19:16.588 --> 19:18.023
- Well, if I'm so bad,

19:18.090 --> 19:21.159
why'd you agree to work with
me in the first place?

19:21.226 --> 19:23.695
- Maybe because we don't hang
out as much anymore.

19:23.762 --> 19:25.964
I liked being a Karate Kid.

19:26.031 --> 19:27.499
- Really?

19:27.566 --> 19:29.167
I had no idea.

19:29.234 --> 19:32.004
- ♪

19:32.070 --> 19:34.773
- CARTER: Did that kid just
walk by with three turtles?

19:34.840 --> 19:37.242
- What could he possibly
do with three tur--

19:37.309 --> 19:40.712
- BOY: [singing opera]
- Oh, my...

19:40.779 --> 19:44.116
- He's juggling the turtles!
- And singing opera!

19:44.182 --> 19:46.585
That kid is amazing at stuff.

19:46.652 --> 19:48.887
I definitely can't beat that.

19:48.954 --> 19:51.089
- I don't think I can
beat that either.

19:51.156 --> 19:52.925
Maybe if we did it together.

19:52.991 --> 19:57.496
- Karate Kids?
- Karate Kids.

19:57.563 --> 19:59.765
- [singing opera continues]

19:59.831 --> 20:01.133
- WOMAN: [announcing]
Attention, everyone!

20:01.199 --> 20:03.702
We only have
ten watches left,

20:03.769 --> 20:07.472
so I'm sorry,
but no one after...

20:07.539 --> 20:10.008
this point is gonna get one.

20:10.075 --> 20:13.245
- Mr. Teddy wants
a watch, too.

20:13.312 --> 20:14.446
- WOMAN:
Awww...

20:14.513 --> 20:18.450
Well, then Mr. Teddy's
gonna get a watch, too.

20:18.517 --> 20:21.787
Okay, so no one
after, um...

20:21.853 --> 20:24.790
this point is gonna
get a watch.

20:26.725 --> 20:28.193
- SAM: Oh, no.

20:28.260 --> 20:30.929
- Don't worry, Sam,
at least you'll get a watch.

20:30.996 --> 20:33.031
Hey, maybe I can come
to your house

20:33.098 --> 20:35.534
on weekends and look at it.

20:35.601 --> 20:39.471
- [sighing] I'm gonna make
sure you guys get watches.

20:39.538 --> 20:42.374
[sighing]

20:42.441 --> 20:44.309
I'm sorry.
- For what?

20:44.376 --> 20:46.144
- For this.

20:46.211 --> 20:47.779
- Mr. Teddy!

20:47.846 --> 20:50.415
Oh, it's on now!

20:50.482 --> 20:54.686
- ♪

20:54.753 --> 20:57.155
- Well, my friends
got their watches

20:57.222 --> 21:00.258
and I got beat down
by a little girl.

21:00.325 --> 21:02.494
Classic win-lose.

21:02.561 --> 21:05.631
- [martial arts grunts]

21:05.697 --> 21:09.067
- [dramatic music]

21:10.235 --> 21:12.804
- That was nice.
- CROWD: [applauding]

21:12.871 --> 21:18.043
[cheering]

21:18.110 --> 21:19.811
- That was amazing!

21:19.878 --> 21:21.980
- The Karate Kids are back!

21:24.449 --> 21:26.918
- Yeah, we still lost.

21:26.985 --> 21:28.787
The kid juggled turtles!

21:28.854 --> 21:30.889
There's no way you're
gonna beat that.

21:30.956 --> 21:33.792
But some things are more
important than fame.

21:33.859 --> 21:35.927
I...I'm talking
about friendship.

21:37.663 --> 21:41.366
Man, when you did
that intense...

21:41.433 --> 21:42.634
That was awesome.

21:42.701 --> 21:44.670
- Yeah, but when you pulled
out those googly eyes,

21:44.736 --> 21:46.238
I almost lost it.

21:46.304 --> 21:47.472
- You know what?

21:47.539 --> 21:49.241
It felt good to be
the Karate Kids again.

21:49.307 --> 21:50.709
- Yeah, it did.

21:50.776 --> 21:51.877
- Wanna go get some pizza?

21:51.943 --> 21:53.178
- That sounds great.

21:53.245 --> 21:54.379
- Pepperoni?

21:54.446 --> 21:56.481
- What? No. Sausage.

21:56.548 --> 21:58.050
- What do you mean, sausage?

21:58.116 --> 22:01.853
- I mean sausage is the best
topping in the world.

22:01.920 --> 22:04.356
- Uh, I don't know if
this is gonna work.

22:06.358 --> 22:22.107
- ♪
